Mix whipped topping and vanilla. Spread 1 Tbsp. of the whipped topping mixture onto each of 20 of the graham squares. Stack grahams together, then stand on edge on serving platter to make an 8-1/2-inch loaf. Frost with remaining whipped topping. Crush remaining 2 graham squares; sprinkle over loaf. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Cut diagonally into 10 slices to serve. Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.